\section{System Architecture}
% -------------------------------------------------------

\subsection{Architecture Overview}
The system is a full-stack web app on Django 4.2 (Python 3.11) backed by MySQL 8.0, organized into five layers. The \textbf{Presentation Layer} (Bootstrap 5.3, vanilla JS) handles question display, answer capture, and the 20-minute countdown, and also enforces a fullscreen gate via the Fullscreen API. A \texttt{navigator.sendBeacon} call auto-submits the test if the tab closes. The \textbf{Controller Layer} (Django views) coordinates the session lifecycle, runs the synchronous rule-based fallback, and spawns the async agent threads. The \textbf{AI/Agent Pipeline Layer} runs the CrewAI pipeline (Evaluator $\rightarrow$ Predictor $\rightarrow$ Overseer) in a daemon thread that talks to Gemini 2.5 Flash through CrewAI's \texttt{LLM} interface. The \textbf{Question Generation Layer} calls Gemini via the \texttt{google-generativeai} SDK to produce MCQs on demand using a strict JSON schema. The \textbf{Data Layer} is three MySQL models: \texttt{StudentTestResult}, \texttt{QuestionPerformance}, and \texttt{AdaptiveLearningHistory}.

